# GNU::FreeFont add-on (ChatGPT)

This bundle adds a routine to `lib/GNU/FreeFont/Subs.rakumod`:

- `pdf-language-samples($font-ref, Str:D $outfile --> IO::Path)`

It renders a **portrait A4** PDF page sequence with page numbers “n of m” at the bottom-right that shows each entry in `%default-samples` with a language label and the sample text, using the selected GNU FreeFont face. The page **title includes the resolved face name** when available.

## Accepted `$font-ref` forms

- `1|2|3` → `FreeSerif`, `FreeSans`, `FreeMono`
- A **family name** like `FreeSans`
- A **path** to a `.ttf`/`.otf` file

## Test

A small test `t/90-pdf-language-samples.t` generates a PDF to `t/out/lang-samples-test.pdf` if a FreeFont face is present on the system. If not installed, it skips gracefully.

## Dependencies

Ensure your `META6.json` includes:

```json
{
  "depends": [
    "PDF::Lite",
    "PDF::Font::Loader"
  ]
}
```

## Install

Paste the routine into your existing `lib/GNU/FreeFont/Subs.rakumod` (or drop this file in place if you prefer to replace) and run:

```
zef test .
```


### Options

- `:page-size<Letter|A4>` (default A4)


## Kerning
- Toggle per call: `:kerning(True|False)` (default: `True`).
- We pass this through to `PDF::Lite` as `:kern($kerning)` when drawing sample text.
